subsection.text:

Section 4022B(a) of the Employee Retirement Income Security Act of 1974 (
  29 U.S.C. 1322b(a)
) is amended by adding at the end the following: If, at the time of termination of a plan under this title, or at the time of freezing benefit accruals under a plan pursuant to subsections (a)(1) and (b) of section 402 of the Pension Protection Act of 2006, regulations prescribed by the Federal Aviation Administration required an individual to separate from service as a commercial airline pilot after attaining any age before age 65, this subsection shall be applied to an individual who is a participant in the plan by reason of such service by substituting such age for age 65..
